      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's exactly what i was thinking. it's not just like, \"hey, this looks pretty,\" it feels more intentional. like if they use these specific grids or patterns in mass-produced clothes, they could basically be installing a subconscious \"compliance mode\" in everyone wearing them. do you think there's a connection between these types of patterns and how big corporations or even governments try to keep the population from questioning things?",
