      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's getting harder to ignore once you see it. i've been noticing that the more \"standard\" or \"basic\" a brand's seasonal collection is, the more intense these patterns seem to be. like, they aren't just selling clothes, they're selling a way to keep us passive. why do you think they specifically choose these high-frequency, repetitive patterns instead of something more chaotic? what's the science behind why that specific visual structure works so effectively for this purpose?",
